# Library Management System

![Java](https://img.shields.io/badge/Java-17-blue)
![Spring Boot](https://img.shields.io/badge/Spring_Boot-2.7.9-green)
![Security](https://img.shields.io/badge/Spring_Security-5.7-yellowgreen)
![WebSocket](https://img.shields.io/badge/WebSocket-STOMP-lightgrey)
![Database](https://img.shields.io/badge/H2-Database-orange)

A full-featured library management system with real-time notifications, user authentication, and administrative controls.

## Features

### üìö Core Functionality

- User authentication with registration/login
- Role-based access control (USER/ADMIN)
- Book catalog management (CRUD operations)
- Book borrowing/returning system
- Search functionality for books

### ‚öôÔ∏è Admin Features

- User management (view/delete users)
- Borrow transaction monitoring
- System statistics dashboard
- Actuator information panel

### üåê Advanced Features

- REST API for books/borrows management
- Real-time WebSocket notifications:
  - New book alerts
  - Book return notifications
- Responsive web interface with Thymeleaf templates

## Technology Stack

- **Backend**:
  - Java 17
  - Spring Boot 2.7.9
  - Spring Security 5.7
  - Spring WebSocket (STOMP)
  - Spring Data JPA
- **Frontend**:
  - Thymeleaf templates
  - Bootstrap 5
  - SockJS + STOMP.js
- **Database**: H2 (in-memory)
- **Build Tool**: Maven

## Dependencies (Key)

```xml
<dependencies>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-actuator</artifactId>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-jpa</artifactId>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-security</artifactId>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-thymeleaf</artifactId>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-websocket</artifactId>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.thymeleaf.extras</groupId>
        <artifactId>thymeleaf-extras-springsecurity5</artifactId>
        <version>3.0.4.RELEASE</version>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>
        <artifactId>h2</artifactId>
        <scope>runtime</scope>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>
```
